## LAYOUT PRINCIPLES
1. Always left-align text and content
2. Use prose paragraphs, avoid bullet lists unless explicitly needed
3. Slide structure: Section header, slide number (bottom right), main content (left-aligned)
4. Generous white space - don't crowd slides
5. Maximum 1 concept per slide

## SLIDE TEMPLATES

### Title Slide
- Large H1 (centered is OK here)
- Subtitle below
- Brand icon optional
- Minimal decoration

### Content Slide (Text Only)
- H3 headline (left-aligned)
- Body text in prose (left-aligned)
- Optional small data visualization

### Content Slide (Text + Image)
- Left column: H3 + prose (60% width)
- Right column: Image/chart (40% width)

### Data Slide
- H3 headline
- Large numbers with context
- Simple chart only (no complex visualizations)

### Section Divider
- Section letter + number (large)
- Section title
- Minimal, clean

### Index/Table of Contents
- Numbered list (exception to no-bullets rule)
- Clean hierarchy
- Page numbers right-aligned

## ANIMATION PRINCIPLES (GSAP)
1. Slide transitions: Fade + subtle slide (not dramatic)
2. Content reveal: Stagger children with 0.1s delay
3. Highlight animations: Scale pulse on key metrics (1.05x scale)
4. Duration: 0.4-0.6s for most animations
5. Easing: power2.out for natural feel

### Example Patterns
Slide entrance: opacity 0→1, y: 20→0, duration: 0.5s
Highlight: scale 1→1.05→1, duration: 0.3s, repeat once

## LANGUAGE-SPECIFIC RULES

### English
- Headings: REM font
- Body: Noto Sans JP font

### Chinese (Traditional & Simplified)
- All text: Noto Sans TC or Noto Sans SC
